text_labels:
Using variables to set up colors provides enhanced flexibility and control over your color scheme. This method allows you to easily adjust colors for any element by using tokens, eliminating the risk of conflicting color configurations.

To change colors, click on your canvas and select Local variables tab in the right sidebar of Figma.

If you need to customize colors or names, find the color you want to modify and click on it. follow these steps:

Edit Colors: Locate the color you want to change and click on it. A color picker will appear, allowing you to choose your desired shade.

Rename Colors: For a more personalized experience, you can change the 

name of the color. Double-click on the current name, and a text field will appear. You can then type in the new name for the color.

To personalize the color scheme for different modes, follow these steps:

Navigate to the Tokens section: You can find this option in the sidebar.
Select Light mode: Adjust the colors according to your preferences for the Light mode.

Select Dark mode: Customize the colors to suit your preferences for the Dark mode.

This allows you to have distinct color schemes for Light and Dark modes, tailored to your liking.
